ach other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Imam Ahmad said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36093,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/companions-taqabbal-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":36091,"position":1},"title":"Sahaba on Eid: May Allah accept from us and you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Jubayr ibn Nufayr reported: The Companions of the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, when they met each other on the day of Eid, they would say to each other, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you.\u201d Source: S\u0323ala\u0304t al-'\u012adayn lil-Mah\u0323a\u0304mili\u0304 2\/218 Grade: Hasan\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36088,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/11\/taqabbal-allahu-minna-minkum\/","url_meta":{"origin":36091,"position":2},"title":"Umar II on Eid: May Allah accept from us and from you","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 11, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Adham reported: We would say to Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, on the two Eids, \u201cMay Allah accept good deeds from us and from you, O commander of the faithful.\u201d He would return it to us and he did not reject that from us. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":20860,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2015\/09\/01\/hasan-everyday-obey-eid\/","url_meta":{"origin":36091,"position":3},"title":"Hasan on Eid: Every day Muslims obey Allah a celebration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 1, 2015","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Rajab reported: Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cEvery day in which Allah is not disobeyed is a celebration. Every day the believer spends in obedience, servitude, remembrance, and gratitude is a celebration.\u201d Source: Lat\u0323a\u0304'if al-Ma'a\u0304rif 1\/278 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0631\u062c\u0628 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0633\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0635\u0631\u064a \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u062a\u0639\u0627\u0644\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":36167,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/05\/15\/every-sinless-day-id\/","url_meta":{"origin":36091,"position":4},"title":"Hasan on Eid: Every day without sin is a celebration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 15, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Shawdhab reported: We were with Al-Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, and he heard a man speaking during Eid. Al-Hasan said, \u201cEvery day in which Allah Almighty is not disobeyed is a celebration.\u201d Source: Musalsal al-\u02bb\u012adayn 28 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0634\u064e\u0648\u0652\u0630\u064e\u0628\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064f\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0627 \u0639\u0650\u0646\u0652\u062f\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19598,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/07\/26\/eid-takbir-imam-arrives\/","url_meta":{"origin":36091,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Eid: Pronouncing Takbir until the Imam arrives","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 26, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Nafi\u2019 reported: Abdullah ibn Umar, may Allah be pleased with him, would depart to the Eid prayer from the mosque and he would raise his voice, declaring the greatness of Allah until he arrived at the place of prayer. He would continue to exalt Allah until the Imam arrived. Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/36091","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https